Port Adelaide is approximately 14 kilometres northwest of the Adelaide CBD. It lies within the City of Port Adelaide Enfield and is the main port for the city of Adelaide. Port Adelaide played an important role in the formative decades of Adelaide and South Australia, with the port being early Adelaide's main supply and information link to the rest of the world.
Pubs in Port Adelaide: Birkenhead Riverview Tavern 1877, The British Hotel 1847, Dockside Tavern 1850, First Commercial Inn 1841, Newmarket Hotel 1879, Port Anchor Hotel 1873, Port Dock Brewery Hotel 1855, Railway Hotel 1856, Royal Arms Hotel 1878 and The Lighthouse Hotel 1857.
Port Adelaide has three shopping centres: Port Canal Shopping Centre; Port Mall; and Fisherman's Wharf Markets.
Port Adelaide is home to the Port Adelaide Football Club, an Australian Rules football team.
Main Tourist Attractions: National Railway Museum, South Australian Maritime Museum, City of Adelaide Clipper, Austbuilt Maritime Museum, Australian Museum of South Australian Aviation, and many historical buildings in Lipson Street, which is in the heart of the Historic Tourism Precinct.

For the benefit of the cooking enthusiast, there is ample bench space for food preparation and plenty of cupboard space for all your storage needs. Additionally, your microwave can be clear from the bench as there is an allocated square in the cabinets to place it 
> continuing through, we find the 3 bedrooms. The master can be found towards the front of the home, featuring a picture window, ceiling fan, built-in robe and a split-system air conditioner
> bedroom 2 & 3 are also of good size & one of which is complete with a built-in robe 
> 3 way bathroom which is ideal for the growing family; to the left is the full-size bathtub & a walk-in shower. Separately, you will find the vanity area and the toilet 
> the rear garden is quite versatile when it comes to hosting friends & family, depending on the time of year. Through the sliding doors from the kitchen, you will find a paved area situated underneath a shade cloth which would be beautiful to host a lunch in the warm summer months. Stepping around the corner to the right is a long verandah, where you can entertain during the cooler months when protection is required  
> plenty of lawn area surrounds the rear yard, where you can enjoy sports with the kids, play with your pets or enjoy a delicious picnic. For those with a 'green-thumb', two sheds in the rear corner of the property provide space to store garden equipment, or for the savvy handyman, tools 
> single carport provides a secure, undercover area to store your car, and for additional driveway space, there is a double-width paved area for two more vehicles. Should you have a caravan or trailer, there is plenty of space to store those too at the front of the property
> the home is situated in close proximity to Aldinga Central Shopping Centre, Aldinga Beach B-7 School as well as the convenience of essential amenities such as shopping, transport and numerous parks & reserves. Aldinga Beach, Port Noarlunga & Christies Esplanade is only a stones-throw away and a 45 minute drive will land you in the Adelaide CBD via the Southern Expressway & Main South Road; it doesn't get much better than this

listing_title: Fabulous Colonial Style Home with Large Rumpas Room or Optional 4th Bedroom
listing_description:
The surprise is definitely inside this lovely family home, and you'll be so impressed! 

Sitting on a 720sqm Allotment, with large rear yard,  the home has been extensively renovated in the past year, with a fresh coat of paint throughout and beautiful polished timber floors in the formal lounge and central passageway. 

The lounge is really spacious and includes a bay window. There are three large bedrooms and they all include built in robes and carpets. 

Directly opposite is the modern bathroom and toilet also renovated with sparkling floor to ceiling tiles and modern fittings. 

The kitchen has been beautifully remodelled with plenty of bench and cupboard space, and will appeal to any budding home chef. You'll love using the top quality European appliances, and matching stainless steel dishwasher. 

A decent sized laundry is also close and handy. 

The rumpus room is huge and could be divided into three rooms. The area is currently set up as a formal dine and big living room with picture windows, combustion heater and downlights, and owners are obtaining quotes to turn this into a fourth bedroom. 

The main part of the home has 9ft ceilings and includes ducted reverse cycle air conditioning and there's a 1.5KW solar power system. Other improvements include a large verandah, triple length carport with auto roller door and there's direct access to a double garage with power and light. The yard is level and private with good size toolshed and plenty of room for kids and pets to play. Located in a good part of the suburb with bus services and local primary and high schools only a short walk away it is a great place to live! For further details please register online to be updated on inspection times.

listing_title: Quality Home close to all amenities
listing_description:
This light & bright courtyard home is situated in a great location. Close to Castle Plaza, Marion Shopping, Finders Uni & Medical Centre, City, transport & schools, it will appeal to both families and couples. Spacious floor plan, with three good sized bedrooms, two bathrooms & a huge open plan kitchen/family/dining space. The garage has direct access to the interior of the home for safety & convenience. 

There are warm toned floating floorboards throughout the home and the colour palette is classic and neutral.
The master bedroom has a walk through robe with generous hanging space. The ensuite has a huge amount of storage in the vanity, frameless glass shower screen & toilet. The bedroom itself has good proportions, double windows and carpet for comfort. Bedrooms two & three also are carpeted and have mirrored built in robes. The main bathroom has a large frameless glass shower, vanity & bath for a relaxing soak. The toilet is separate. The laundry has direct access to the outside clothes line. It has more storage options and bench space for folding & sorting.

The main attraction of this lovely home is the spacious open plan kitchen/family/dining space. It is filled with natural light and has glass sliding doors that bring the outside in. The stylish, two toned kitchen is sleek & modern with ample bench & cupboard space. There is a LG dishwasher, stainless steel gas cook top and oven, double sink and generous fridge space. There is a large island bench that doubles as a breakfast bar.

The rear yard has been landscaped with easy maintenance plants. There is a pergola with paved entertaining space and a streamlined rain water tank. The climate is controlled by two efficient inverter r/c split system air conditioners. There is a Rinnai hot water system with temperature control panel.

There is no expense spared in this luxury home and you have the opportunity to call it home.  Offering a gourmet kitchen  with Smeg appliances, stone benchtops and conveniently concealed butler's pantry and laundry.

Surrounded by floor to ceiling windows the home beams with natural light. The undercover alfresco is positioned to host many gatherings with the in-built kitchen before you migrate to the glistening swimming pool to cool off with a splash. If you feel like relaxing the pool can be turned into a spa with 12 jets around the seated area. There is even a low-maintenance patch of lawn making this all about lifestyle and less work.

Upsatirs offers a generous size master or a haven for parents - complete with a makeup nook naturally lit to perfection, walk-in robe with in-built jewellery drawer and luxe ensuite with double vanity, dual rain shower heads and opulent stand-alone tub.

The positioning of the home itself provides you with the privilege of a short morning commute to the CBD and an even shorter evening stroll to feel the sand between your toes whilst experiencing those magical beachy sunsets and getting your daily steps up.

The booming area of  Henley Square continues to bloom, guaranteeing your weekends are well spent with endless options for coffee, dinner, drinks and ice-cream dates alike.

If Golf is for you then the Kooyonga Golf Course, Adelaide's most prestigious private Golf Club and popular amongst golf's elite is virtually at your back door.
More to love:
- Flexible floorplan with five bedrooms and multiple living areas
- Scope for downstairs bedroom/ theatre room, playroom/study and living areas
- Three-way main bathroom with separate tub services the upper level
- Double garage with internal access, sensor lights and smart phone control kit
- Powerful ducted reverse cycle air conditioning powered by AirTouch temperature control system
- Gas fire warms both the open plan living and alfresco
- Security system
- Heated magnesium pool and spa
- Self irrigated garden
- Abundance of storage throughout
- Square set ceilings, plush carpets and timber floors
- Short 15-minute commute to the CBD
- Public transport at the end of the street
- Proximity to the shopping amenities of Henley Foodland and Harbour Town
- First class education is a short ride away at Lockleys and Fulham North Primary, St. Michael's Secondary, St. Francis and Star of the Sea
